<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06354139 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06354139 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  It was on this date in 1732 that Benjamin Franklin adopted the pen name ofRichard Saunders and began work on &quot;Poor Richard's Almanack,&quot; providinginspiration for certain imitators to follow as inevitably as vultures follow ascent. It was in this almanac, published every year from 1733 until 1758, thatsuch items of wisdom as &quot;A penny faved is a penny earned&quot; and &quot;God helps themthat help themfelves&quot; first appeared. The philosophy these aphorismsrepresented had a deep influence on subsequent American thought . . . but thefpelling came in for a few changes.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  OUR OWN ALMANAC  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  People .; Information in this column is from Mercury news wire services.  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Jim Jeffress  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911219  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  109  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, December 19, 199100354139,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>